Parts/Description/solararray_3v_large: The SP-XXL is a breakthrough in solar panel technology. It is not just 1.5 times larger than the “Gigantor,” it uses a completely new deployment design that promises to be stronger and safer than previous models.
Parts/Description/stabilizer_0v_flybywir: After scientist Bob Kerman’s first and last flying lesson, a colleague from C7 reached out with an idea he had been working on: the CH-J3. This ingenious Fly-By-Wire Aircraft Stabilizer fits onto any craft and can assist even the clumsiest kerbal into becoming a capable pilot.
Parts/Description/stabilizer_0v_reaction: Built to add stability to a small craft, the TRW-0625 uses micro-gyroscopic technology to generate the torque necessary to control a spacecraft without wasting any propellant. It absolutely is not a sit and spin.
Parts/Description/stabilizer_1v_procedur: Control is everything when you are flying, and this miraculous little stabilizer is well up to the task. Transform your craft into something special with the LPS-250 “Transform” stabilizers, available in any shape you can imagine.
Parts/Description/stabilizer_1v_reaction: The SRW-125 uses several internal reaction wheels to generate enough torque to keep a medium-sized craft under control. These larger wheels are driven by proportionally larger motors, so remember to keep an eye on your electricity levels. Batteries not included.
Parts/Description/stabilizer_2v_procedur: The MPS-500 is one of the most advanced aerodynamic stabilizing systems available today. Using a unique combination of CNC lathes, laser routers, and a generous amount of duct tape, we can build whatever you desire.

Control is everything when you are flying, and this miraculous little stabilizer is well up to the task. Transform your craft into something special with the LPS-250 “Transform” stabilizers, available in any shape you can imagine.
Parts/Description/stabilizer_2v_reaction: The MRW-250 is a powerful reaction wheel designed to keep your craft stable without wasting precious RCS propellant. It does consume a lot of electricity, but we promise that was not to help Probodobodyne increase solar panel sales.
Parts/Description/stabilizer_3v_procedur: The MPS-500 is one of the most advanced aerodynamic stabilizing systems available today. Using a unique combination of CNC lathes, laser routers, and a generous amount of duct tape, we can build whatever you desire.

When it comes time to keep your really large aircraft flying straight, hire a good pilot and slap on the HPS-1000. Do not order a control surface shaped like a good pilot: that is not very aerodynamic.
Parts/Description/stabilizer_3v_reaction: The LRW-375 uses four gyroscopes working in sync to provide an impressive amount of torque and stability in even the largest craft. It will also eat your batteries like candy while in use.
Parts/Description/storage_0v_battery_ele: What do toys, flashlights, and rockets all have in common? They all need batteries. The Z-200 is built for just this purpose, and fits nicely into a very small rocket stack. Remember to keep your batteries charged!

The Z-100 is a radially mounted, rechargeable battery, and it is the standard for most Kerbal craft. The Z-100 holds a small amount of electricity. These batteries are fragile, so protect them well if you don't want the power to go out at an inopportune time.
Parts/Description/storage_1v_battery_ele: The Z-1K is a heavy-duty rechargeable battery, designed to fit into a small rocket stack. It is more rugged than its smaller counterparts, but we recommend not throwing rocks at it.

The Z-400 is a radially mounted battery for when a conventional Z-100 will not suffice. Large and versatile, this battery can be used for a variety of tasks. Please, in case of emergency, do not reverse the polarity.
Parts/Description/storage_2v_battery_ele: The Z-4K is one of the largest batteries ever conceived by Zaltonic, and it is designed to fit perfectly into a medium rocket stack. While it is very durable, it should be treated with respect and not used to produce artificial lightning, no matter how fun that sounds.
Parts/Description/storage_3v_battery_ele: Rumors that the Z-375 is a used decoupler stuffed with smaller batteries are true, but that does not diminish its effectiveness.
Parts/Description/storage_4v_battery_ele: The ZX-10K is a huge and powerful battery that can store more electricity than you will probably ever use. Unfortunately, the name is incorrect and should be Z-5X. The writer responsible will be docked a month worth of snacks.
Parts/Description/strut_1v_extensible: Commonly referred to as “Space Tape” the EAS-4 Strut Connector is designed to create a strong connection between two parts, allowing for sturdier (and heavier) construction. Trust us, this will soon become your favorite part.
Parts/Description/tailsection_1v_tapered: The Tail Connector A is one of the few parts manufactured by the beloved WinterOwl Aircraft Emporium, made exclusively for the back end of an aircraft. It could easily be manufactured by anyone, but everyone loves WinterOwl, so it’s never been copied.
The Slanted Tail Connector B offers an option for aircraft tail assemblies. Or if you want a really, really long nose on your aircraft. It’s your craft, build it like you want.
Parts/Description/truss_0v_square_1x1: The ST-XS-1 is a tiny square truss measuring 0.625 meters in length. Rumor is it became known as the “Boxy Delight” after an engineer accidentally welded themselves inside one during assembly.
Parts/Description/truss_0v_square_1x1_0-: The ST-Micro-1 is a square micro-truss measuring 0.3125 meters in length. It is affectionately known as the “Tinker-truss” among several prominent construction companies.
Parts/Description/truss_0v_square_1x4: The ST-XS-4 is a tiny square truss measuring 2.5 meters in length. It is extremely useful for smaller craft. While it may look like a ladder, this is assuredly not a ladder and Bob's Girders is not responsible for ladder-based usage.
Parts/Description/truss_0v_square_1x4_0-: The ST-125-Micro is a square micro-truss measuring 1.25 meters in length. This small but sturdy truss is popular both for ship design as well as some very attractive modern art sculptures.
Parts/Description/truss_1v_circular_1x1: The CT-S-1 is a small circular truss measuring 1.25 meters in length. It was designed for smaller craft but is also very popular for construction team bosses to stand on during meetings.
Parts/Description/truss_1v_circular_1x4: The CT-S-4 is a small circular truss measuring 5 meters in length. It is very handy for smaller craft and after-work log rolling competitions.
Parts/Description/truss_1v_square_1x1: The ST-S-1 is a small square truss measuring 1.25 meters in length. We’re told it was actually built to be a large seafood trap.
Parts/Description/truss_1v_square_1x4: The ST-S-4 is a small square truss measuring 5 meters in length. It was designed for use with construction cranes but works equally well on spacecraft.
Parts/Description/truss_2v_circular_1x1: The CT-M-1 is a medium circular truss measuring 2.5 meters in length. It is designed for spacecraft and boasts some of the most perfect circles in truss history.
Parts/Description/truss_2v_circular_1x4: The CT-M-4 is a medium circular truss measuring 10 meters in length. It is vey useful for all sorts of spacecraft design. Toes be warned, they tend to roll around on the ground.
Parts/Description/truss_2v_saddle_1x1: The MST-S is a marvel in engineering. Lightweight but incredibly strong, it is a cargo hold made of tubes. Who would have thought it possible? The team at Tubular Tubes, that’s who!
Parts/Description/truss_2v_saddle_1x4: The MST-L Saddle Truss is longer, stronger, and more tubular than the MST-M.
Parts/Description/truss_2v_square_1x1: The ST-M-1 is a medium square truss measuring 2.5 meters in length. The R&D team boasts it could even support the weight of a full-grown Kraken. No one wants to test this.
Parts/Description/truss_2v_square_1x4: The ST-M-4 is a medium square truss measuring 10 meters in length. On ground or in space, it has the most beautiful rivets around.
Parts/Description/truss_3v_circular_1x1: The CT-L-1 is a large circular truss measuring 3.75 meters in length. Marketing has coined this truss “Circle Me Around,” but we’re not sure why.
Parts/Description/truss_3v_circular_1x4: The CT-L-4 is a large circular truss measuring 15 meters in length. It was supposed to be a 1.5-meter circular stage truss, but one of the engineers read the blueprint wrong, and hundreds were manufacturered before the mistake was caught.
Parts/Description/truss_3v_saddle_1x1: The LST-S is a second-generation saddle truss. Not only is it designed to hold and discard whatever cargo you want to carry, it is also designed with even more tubes that the MST series!
Parts/Description/truss_3v_saddle_1x4: The LST-L saddle truss, lightweight and strong, is perfect for long voyages. It can hold whatever you like for as long as you like, so what's not to like?
Parts/Description/truss_3v_square_1x1: The ST-L-1 is a large square truss measuring 3.75 meters in length. It comes in one color, and any attempt to change the color will void the warranty.
Parts/Description/truss_3v_square_1x4: The ST-L-4 is a large square truss measuring 15 meters in length and a popular choice for making large spacecraft larger.
Parts/Description/truss_4v_circular_1x1: The CT-XL-1 is a huge circular truss measuring 5 meters in length. Oddly, no one has proposed a nickname.
Parts/Description/truss_4v_circular_1x4: The CT-XL-4 is a huge circular truss measuring 20 meters in length. This truss is so big it’s been dubbed the “Circulator.” We told marketing that this would be confusing, but never argue with Bob.
Parts/Description/truss_4v_saddle_1x1: It might look like just a framework, but the HST-S is one of the most reliable saddle trusses available. R&D assures us that according to their new tubmatics formula, it has the shiniest tubes available.
Parts/Description/truss_4v_saddle_1x4: When Tubular Tubes first proposed the HST-L saddle, engineers wondered who would use such a monstrosity. When one was used to transport tons of emergency snacks to a colony on the Mun, it became huge success, even starring in an upcoming action movie!
Parts/Description/truss_4v_square_1x1: The ST-XL-1 is a huge square truss measuring 5 meters in length. It is so huge and square that it’s been granted no less than 4 honorable mentions from the Kerbal Cubist society.
Parts/Description/truss_4v_square_1x4: The ST-XL-4 is a huge square truss measuring 20 meters in length. This truss is so big it could be the frame for a skyscraper. No, we did not steal this from an actual skyscraper.
Parts/Description/tube_0v_procedural: The TOOB-000 may seem small, but it is both lightweight and strong, and so much cooler than a truss. (Don’t tell the folks at Bob’s Girders we said that)
Parts/Description/tube_1v_procedural: The TOOB-125 was one of the first tubes Tubular Tubes manufactured and continues to be one of the best-selling TOOB tubes on the market. Because TOOB tubes are the coolest tubes to be. (Apologies, marketing made us say that.)
Parts/Description/tube_2v_procedural: The TOOB-250 is designed for all your tubular construction needs. Because everyone knows a ship is much cooler when it has TOOB tubes.
Parts/Description/tube_3v_procedural: When it comes to structural tubes, the TOOB-375 is one of the most tubular tubes available. Lightweight, strong, and oh, so cool, it is guaranteed to make any construction project look better.
Parts/Description/tube_4v_procedural: Everyone knows a tube is lighter, stronger and much cooler than a cylinder, and the TOOB-500 is a perfect example. By far one of the most popular TOOB tubes in Tubular Tube’s tube inventory.
Parts/Description/wheel_0v_rover: The S2 rover wheel is the smallest in Kerbal Motion’s inventory. Lightweight and strong, the S2 was designed for exploration vehicles, but it works well for smaller one- or two-seat rovers. Just don’t try any fancy maneuvers.
Parts/Description/wheel_1v_rover: The RoveMax M1 is the perfect balance of both strength and style. Whether you’re designing a sophisticated exploration craft or building a giant skateboard, this medium-sized rover wheel is an excellent choice to keep on rollin'.
Parts/Description/wheel_2v_rover_ruggedi: Using the latest ruggedizing technology, the engineers at Kerbal Motion developed the ultra-rugged TR-2L “Ruggedized” rover wheel. This medium rover wheel is so tough and rugged we just can’t say it enough. For the best in off-world off-road fun, go with the TR-2L.
Parts/Description/wheel_2v_truck: When you need to haul large amounts of cargo or passengers, look to the RoveMax TR4 truck wheels. Designed for the cruelest terrain, the TR4 is large enough to crush smaller rovers in their tracks. Please, don’t crush any small rovers. Our stockholders hate that.
Parts/Description/wheel_3v_rover: The RoveMax XL3 motorized rover wheels are the largest and heaviest rover wheels available. Rumors that they were so huge the Kerbal Motion CEO had a heart attack when he first saw them are greatly exaggerated. Truth be told, he only fainted. Twice.
Parts/Description/wing_1v_procedural_lig: The LPW-250 is a lightweight wing that can be designed and built for smaller aircraft of any style. Whether it’s a straight wing, tapered, elliptical, or some new name you make up, we here at Wingit can build it. Except inside-out. We don’t recommend that.
Parts/Description/wing_2v_procedural_hea: The MPW-500 is truly a metamorphic wonder wing, and a great choice for any medium sized aircraft. No matter what design you desire, we can manufacture it. Whether it will fly exactly the way you want, well, that's up to you!

It can be built to accommodate large cargo craft, passenger jets, and even massive SSTO’s. Bring us your blueprint, schematic, or napkin sketch, and we’ll make it a reality.

Parts/Description/engine_1v_methalox_cor: Why would Ionic Symphonic ask Jeb’s Junkyard to design their own deep space engine? So their musicians could perform off-world, of course!
Parts/Manufacturer/engine_1v_methalox_co: Jebediah Kerman’s Junkyard and Spacecraft Parts Co.
Parts/Description/engine_2v_methalox_tru: When the CEO of Ionic Symphonic Protonic Electronics commissioned Jebediah’s Junkyard to build an deep space engine, the business world was confused. It made a little more sense when the engine name was revealed.
Parts/Manufacturer/engine_2v_methalox_tr: Jebediah Kerman’s Junkyard and Spacecraft Parts Co.
Parts/Description/engine_3v_methalox_tub: Unlike its namesake, the LV-3000 "Tuba" is elegant and graceful and designed for superior performance in a vacuum. Funded heavily by Ionic Symphonic Protonic Electronics, this beautiful monster is manufactured to haul an entire orchestra to other worlds with ease.
Parts/Manufacturer/engine_3v_methalox_tu: Jebediah Kerman’s Junkyard and Spacecraft Parts Co.
Parts/Description/fueltank_3v_inline_met: It is rumored the extra-long S3-28800 methalox fuel tank is just a pair S3-14400 fuel tanks welded together. Kerbodyne wouldn’t do that just to get a jump on their competitor Rockomax, would they?
Parts/Description/airbrake_1v: After numerous requests from Kerbal pilots to slow a plane down, C7 created a part that replicates a shoddily-welded hull on demand. Focus group testing continues in order to find a shorter name for the Aerodynamically Integrated Retrograde Braking Robustly Armed Kinetic Extending System.
Parts/Description/gridfin_1v_radial: The GRFN provides both drag and steering ability to a craft. It is a very intentional part and was in no way inspired by a faulty airbrake.
Parts/Description/gridfin_2v_radial: The GRFN-250 is designed to help booster recovery by providing drag and some steering control. C7 insists it was not designed as a response to recent competitor WingIt Enterprises’ procedural engineering.
Parts/Description/fueltank_5v_inline_hyd: The HFT “Sphereotron” is a massive in-line hydrogen fuel tank designed for very large interplanetary and interstellar craft. We’re not really sure where the name came from. No one will admit to it.
Parts/Description/radiator_1v_deployable: Designed using multiple liquid cooled radiator panels, the RP-D-10 is fully deployable, adds a fashionable look to any craft, and keeps all of your precious electronics and other temperature sensitive equipment safe.
Parts/Description/radiator_1v_panel: The RP-10 was designed to keep all your precious Probodobodyne electronic parts from overheating, and it will protect the rest of your craft as a bonus.
Parts/Description/radiator_1v_paneledge: The RP-E-10 is an edge-mounted variation of the popular RP-10 radiator, designed to reflect heat away from sensitive equipment. We may be sad that they cannot also be wings, but they are still splendid radiators.
Parts/Description/radiator_2v_deployable: The RP-D-25 deployable radiator uses a myriad of liquid cooled radiator panels to radiate heat away from your craft. These beautiful radiators can even keep some larger engines at a safe temperature. Our designer ensured they look great with some large solar panels.
Parts/Description/radiator_2v_panel: The RP-25 is a radially-mounted radiator panel designed to channel and dissipate heat into the vacuum of space. It is designed to mount flush to any large cylindrical object, and is much more sturdy than its extendable counterparts.
Parts/Description/radiator_3v_deployable: With the advancement of larger and hotter rocket engines, the RP-D-37 is in greater and greater demand. These huge radiators are fully deployable and are a must for interplanetary crafts. Buy yours today before they sell out.
Parts/Description/collector_0v_radial_sc: The RSCM-01 is a small radial collection module that can be configured to meet all your science needs. It can even obtain its own samples using a facinating grabbing arm. Do not use the sample grabber to grab snacks, they foul up the instrumentation.
The RGSCM-01 is a miniaturized GSCM-01, designed to perfrom the same experiment. Data reports are not miniaturized, so put the glasses away.
The ASCM-B is a small science sampling module that can be radially attached. Even though it is both stylish and functional, do not wear it like a backpack.
Parts/Description/collector_1v_radial_sc: Packed with all the science equipment we could think of, the OSCM-01 is designed to collect and process samples of most anything in low or high orbit. Sure, the shape is somewhat is odd, but look at all of that gold foil!
Parts/Description/collector_0v_science_r: The WSRL-01 is designed to collect and process radiation samples across a wide spectrum of frequencies, both locally and in deep space. It is so sensitive that it can even detect and measure the very faint cosmic background radiation signature. But it can’t be used to microwave snacks, so don’t try.
Parts/Description/lab_2v_science_orbital: When a remote science probe just isn’t enough, then the OSL-25 “Starlab” might be just what you’re looking for. This spacious module is packed with all the science tech we could think of: thermometer, barometer, magnetometer, algea container, and, of course, a canister of mystery goo. It even has cup holders!
Parts/Description/lab_2v_science_marine: When Kerbals first discovered a liquid ocean on both Laythe and Eve, the R&D team at Seabug Sciences modified one of their deep-sea probes. It can analyze an alien ocean environment for both its chemical composition and yummy shellfish life signs.
Parts/Description/collector_1v_science_g: The GSCM-01 is a favorite for smaller satellites and landers. Designed to be completely configurable, the “Science Jr” can be outfitted with everything but the kitchen sink, if the kitchen sink had scientific value.
Parts/Description/collector_0v_science_a: The ASCM-A is a self-contained atmospheric lab built into a nose-cone configuration. Useful and stylish, it can collect a wealth of scientific information from any atmosphere you happen to be flying in.
